2026 Regular Session ENROLLED
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 127
BY SENATOR KLEINPETER
A RESOLUTION
To commend Addis, Louisiana resident Jensen LeBlanc upon being named a Children's
Miracle Network National Champion and to recognize his courage, perseverance,
and inspiring impact on others.
WHEREAS, Jensen LeBlanc, an eleven-year-old resident of Addis, Louisiana, has
been selected as a National Champion for Children's Miracle Network Hospitals, one of only
twenty children nationwide chosen to serve as ambassadors for children treated at member
hospitals across the United States; and
WHEREAS, Jensen was diagnosed at just seven months old with croup and stridor,
a rare condition that makes breathing difficult, and has endured significant medical
challenges from an early age; and
WHEREAS, through his treatment journey at Our Lady of the Lake Children's
Hospital, Jensen demonstrated extraordinary resilience and positivity, previously being
named a local Children's Miracle Network Champion in both 2023 and 2024 before
advancing to the national level; and
WHEREAS, Jensen's outlook on life, marked by optimism and a determination to
make the best of difficult circumstances, has inspired medical professionals, community
leaders, and all who have encountered his story; and
WHEREAS, in recognition of his achievement and character, officials in both East
Baton Rouge Parish and West Baton Rouge Parish proclaimed February 23, 2026, as "Jensen
LeBlanc Day," and he was presented with a key to the town of Addis by Mayor David
Toups; and
WHEREAS, Jensen has embraced his role as a national ambassador by sharing his
story to inspire other children facing medical adversity and by promoting support for
children's hospitals; and
WHEREAS, Jensen aspires to become a pediatric surgeon and give back by helping
children facing challenges similar to his own; and
